description: Number of partitions of n into parts not of form 4k+2, 20k, 20k+1 or 20k-1. Also number of partitions in which no odd part is repeated, with no part of size less than or equal to 2 and where differences between parts at distance 4 are greater than 1 when the smallest part is odd and greater than 2 when the smallest part is even.
references: G. E. Andrews, The Theory of Partitions, Addison-Wesley, 1976, p. 114.
